            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed text-black" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                        How is this law applied?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                    <div class="accordion-body">The penalization of programmed obsolescence offers a real opportunity to assert consumer rights and protect the environment against these abusive practices. The offence makes it possible to sanction a practice that in the past could be qualified as a commercial strategy. Note that since the Hamon law, if an individual consumer does not have the means to initiate a procedure and collect the necessary evidence, an approved consumer association can do it for him.  This is why we want to refer a large community of consumers and collect data on cases of programmed obsolescence in order to eventually lead group actions in court.
                        The repression of this crime requires proof of the "deliberate" intention to reduce the life of the product "to increase the replacement rate".  While this may seem difficult to prove, it actually depends on the interpretation of the judges.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
